Trim 3/4 inch from ends of ladyfingers; place ends on bottom of 9-inch springform pan. Stand remaining ladyfingers around side of pan, with cut sides facing in. Reserve 2 strawberries for garnish; mash remaining strawberries. Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl at least 2 minutes until completely dissolved. Add ice cubes; stir until melted. Add whipped topping and mashed strawberries; stir gently with wire whisk until well blended. Refrigerate 10 min. or until mixture is very thick and will mound. Spoon into prepared pan. Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm. Remove side of pan. Top with reserved strawberries.